latestPosts.caption:
Superfood drumstick thogail for lunch today. It’s like a chutney I eat with hot rice.
I’m eating it with a sprouted horsegram ghee rice and a pomelo peanut salad!

For the thogail:
I pressure cook the drumstick with some rock salt and turmeric with very little water (don’t waste the nutrients) for two whistles 

Then I sautee some dry red chillies, garlic and Chana dal in oil and add it to my blender
I separately cook the baby onions and curry leaves and add that as well along with some soaked brindleberry (Malabar tamarind)

I blend it without water and add the scraped drumstick to it, salt as you need :) (add ur leftover drumstick water as well)

@sprite_india found her at Goa but I hope you find her everywhere.

latestPosts.caption:
South Indian raw jackfruit curry in a tangy coconut base. I love anything with coconut milk 💸💸 🥥 

Recipe: 
In coconut oil,
Mustard seeds 
Fenugreek seeds
Curry leaves
2 Green chilli
1 medium Onion

To blend,
2 tomatoes
Few garlic
1/2 inch of ginger
Turmeric powder
Chilli powder
I cook it down until the raw smell disappears

Then I add in an amla size tamarind soaked water
Followed by 1 to 1.5 cups of thick coconut milk (full fat)

Then I add in 200g of cut raw jackfruit and cook in on low for 45 minutes, you might need to add a little water in-between as coconut milk evaporates, don’t forget to salt :)

I top it with some fresh coriander and slivers of fresh ginger
So good
There’s always music in my head
